            <li><a href="#success-criteria">Success Criteria</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Prerequisites -->
    <div class="content-section">
        <h2 id="prerequisites">✅ Prerequisites (From December 26)</h2>

        <div class="alert alert-success">
            <p><strong>This plan assumes Dec 26 results:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>✅ All 6-7 AI Chat tables exist and verified</li>
                <li>✅ Table schemas match Result class definitions</li>
                <li>✅ Test chat messages successfully saved to database</li>
                <li>✅ Messages persist across page reloads</li>
                <li>✅ Basic query and retrieval tests pass</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <p><strong>If any prerequisite failed on Dec 26:</strong> Work through the <a href="/Documentation/Daily_Plans-2025-12-26#next-steps">Dec 26 Next Steps (Debug Path)</a> first, then return to this plan when ready.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Phase 1: Documentation Search -->
    <div class="content-section">
        <h2 id="phase-1-doc-search">🔍 Phase 1: Documentation Search Testing (FULLTEXT Search Index)</h2>

        <div class="phase-status">
            <span class="status-badge pending">EXECUTE TODAY</span>
            <p><strong>Execution:</strong> Test documentation metadata indexing and FULLTEXT search</p>
            <p><strong>Duration Est.:</strong> 45 minutes</p>
        </div>

        <h3>Purpose</h3>
        <p>The <code>documentation_metadata_index</code> table enables AI to search through the application's .tt documentation files. This phase verifies the search index is populated and working correctly.</p>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 1.1: Verify Index Is Populated</h4>
            <p><strong>Check how many documentation files are indexed:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SELECT COUNT(*) as total_docs, 
       COUNT(DISTINCT file_path) as unique_files,
       MIN(indexed_at) as oldest_index,
       MAX(indexed_at) as newest_index
FROM documentation_metadata_index;</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Expected Result:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>✓ Should find 50+ documentation files indexed (Comserv has 314+ .tt files)</li>
                <li>✓ Indexed timestamps should be recent (from Dec 26 or later, depending on when indexing ran)</li>
                <li>✓ Various file paths from different documentation sections</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="color: #721c24; background: #f8d7da; padding: 10px; border-radius: 3px; margin-top: 10px;">
                <strong>⚠️ If Index Empty:</strong> Documentation indexing hasn't run yet. This is okay; can proceed with manual trigger in Task 1.3.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 1.2: Inspect Sample Documentation Entry</h4>
            <p><strong>Look at one indexed documentation file:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SELECT id, file_path, title, excerpt, role_access, file_size, indexed_at
FROM documentation_metadata_index 
LIMIT 1\G</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Verify Fields Are Populated:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>✓ file_path: Full path like "Documentation/AI_Chat_Schema_Documentation"</li>
                <li>✓ title: Human-readable title from META block</li>
                <li>✓ excerpt: First 200 chars of content</li>
                <li>✓ role_access: Roles that can see this doc (admin, developer, user)</li>
                <li>✓ file_size: Bytes in the original file</li>
                <li>✓ searchable_text: FULLTEXT indexed content (check below in Task 1.4)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 1.3: Test FULLTEXT Search</h4>
            <p><strong>Search for documentation containing specific keywords:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SELECT id, file_path, title, MATCH(searchable_text) AGAINST('database' IN BOOLEAN MODE) as relevance_score
FROM documentation_metadata_index 
WHERE MATCH(searchable_text) AGAINST('database' IN BOOLEAN MODE)
ORDER BY relevance_score DESC
LIMIT 10;</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Test Multiple Searches (Run 3-4 different searches):</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Search "database" - Should find schema, ENCY, BMaster docs</li>
                <li>Search "authentication" - Should find auth, user management, login docs</li>
                <li>Search "todo" - Should find todo system, project management docs</li>
                <li>Search "theme" - Should find theme system documentation</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="color: #155724; background: #d4edda; padding: 10px; border-radius: 3px; margin-top: 10px;">
                <strong>✅ Success:</strong> FULLTEXT search returns relevant documentation with scores (higher = more relevant).
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 1.4: Test Role-Based Access Filtering</h4>
            <p><strong>Verify documentation access control works:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>-- Find docs accessible to 'developer' role
SELECT file_path, title, role_access
FROM documentation_metadata_index 
WHERE role_access LIKE '%developer%'
LIMIT 5;

-- Find docs accessible to 'user' role only (most restricted)
SELECT file_path, title, role_access
FROM documentation_metadata_index 
WHERE role_access = 'user'
LIMIT 5;</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Verify:</strong> Different documentation has appropriate role restrictions (admin docs not visible to users, technical docs visible to developers, etc.)</p>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 1.5: Test Documentation Index from UI</h4>
            <p><strong>If AI Chat has a search interface:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to /ai or /Documentation/AI in Comserv</li>
                <li>Try searching for "database" in the documentation search</li>
                <li>Verify search results show relevant documentation</li>
                <li>Click on a result and verify correct document opens</li>
                <li>Try several different search terms</li>
            </ol>

            <p style="color: #721c24; background: #f8d7da; padding: 10px; border-radius: 3px;">
                <strong>Record Results:</strong> How many results per search? Are results relevant? Does clicking results work?
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Phase 2: Code Search -->
    <div class="content-section">
        <h2 id="phase-2-code-search">💻 Phase 2: Code Search Testing (Developer Code Index)</h2>

        <div class="phase-status">
            <span class="status-badge pending">EXECUTE TODAY</span>
            <p><strong>Execution:</strong> Test code search index for developers</p>
            <p><strong>Duration Est.:</strong> 30 minutes</p>
        </div>

        <h3>Purpose</h3>
        <p>The <code>code_search_index</code> table helps developers find functions, classes, and methods. This phase tests that code is properly indexed and searchable.</p>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 2.1: Check Code Index Population</h4>
            <p><strong>Verify code files are indexed:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SELECT COUNT(*) as total_files,
       COUNT(DISTINCT file_path) as unique_files,
       GROUP_CONCAT(DISTINCT file_type) as file_types,
       MIN(indexed_at) as oldest_index,
       MAX(indexed_at) as newest_index
FROM code_search_index;</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Expected Result:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>✓ 50+ Perl files (.pm) indexed</li>
                <li>✓ 50+ Template files (.tt) indexed</li>
                <li>✓ 10+ SQL files (.sql) indexed</li>
                <li>✓ Timestamps recent</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>If Empty:</strong> Code indexing hasn't run. This is normal; can proceed with manual indexing trigger.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 2.2: Inspect Code Index Entry</h4>
            <p><strong>Look at a Perl controller file entry:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SELECT id, file_path, file_type, code_elements, searchable_code, indexed_at
FROM code_search_index 
WHERE file_type = 'pm' 
LIMIT 1\G</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Verify:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>✓ code_elements is valid JSON with function/method names</li>
                <li>✓ searchable_code contains function definitions</li>
                <li>✓ file_path shows actual controller path (e.g., lib/Comserv/Controller/Admin.pm)</li>
                <li>✓ min_role indicates who can see this code (admin/developer)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 2.3: Test Code Search</h4>
            <p><strong>Search for specific methods or functions:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>-- Search for "create_conversation" function
SELECT id, file_path, file_type, MATCH(searchable_code) AGAINST('create_conversation' IN BOOLEAN MODE) as score
FROM code_search_index 
WHERE MATCH(searchable_code) AGAINST('create_conversation' IN BOOLEAN MODE)
LIMIT 5;

-- Search for "BelongsTo" relationship declaration
SELECT id, file_path, file_type
FROM code_search_index 
WHERE MATCH(searchable_code) AGAINST('BelongsTo' IN BOOLEAN MODE)
LIMIT 10;</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Test Multiple Code Searches:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Search "sub list" - Find list methods in controllers</li>
                <li>Search "my $self" - Find method definitions</li>
                <li>Search "DBIx::Class" - Find model definitions</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 2.4: Test Code Metadata Extraction</h4>
            <p><strong>Verify code_elements JSON is properly formatted:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SELECT file_path, code_elements
FROM code_search_index 
WHERE code_elements IS NOT NULL 
  AND JSON_LENGTH(code_elements) > 0
LIMIT 3\G</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Verify JSON Structure:</strong> Should contain objects with: function_name, line_number, type (sub, method, class, etc.)</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Phase 3: Integration Testing -->
    <div class="content-section">
        <h2 id="phase-3-integration">🔗 Phase 3: System Integration Testing (Chat + Search + Context)</h2>

        <div class="phase-status">
            <span class="status-badge pending">EXECUTE TODAY - IMPORTANT</span>
            <p><strong>Execution:</strong> Test AI Chat system works with all search indexes</p>
            <p><strong>Duration Est.:</strong> 60 minutes</p>
        </div>

        <h3>Purpose</h3>
        <p>Verify the AI Chat system can use documentation search, code search, and web search together. This is the core value of the AI Chat feature.</p>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 3.1: Test AI Request with Documentation Search</h4>
            <p><strong>Send a chat request that requires documentation search:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>Open AI Chat interface (http://localhost:5000/ai)</li>
                <li>Ask a question like: "How does the Todo system work?"</li>
                <li>Note the request in the chat</li>
                <li>Let AI respond</li>
            </ol>

            <p><strong>Verify in Database:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>-- Find the chat message with search context
SELECT id, user_id, content, search_context, sources_cited, created_at
FROM ai_messages 
WHERE role = 'user' 
  AND content LIKE '%Todo%'
ORDER BY created_at DESC 
LIMIT 1\G</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Check:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>✓ Message was saved</li>
                <li>✓ Assistant response also saved (should be next message)</li>
                <li>✓ search_context shows which docs were searched</li>
                <li>✓ sources_cited lists documentation sources found</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 3.2: Test AI Request with Code Search</h4>
            <p><strong>Ask about code implementation:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>Send: "Show me how the Todo controller creates a new todo"</li>
                <li>Note if AI can find and reference code</li>
                <li>Verify search_context includes code_search_index references</li>
            </ol>

            <p><strong>Database Verification:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>-- Check if code search results were cited
SELECT search_context, sources_cited
FROM ai_messages 
WHERE role = 'assistant' 
  AND sources_cited LIKE '%code_search%'
ORDER BY created_at DESC 
LIMIT 1\G</code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 3.3: Test Conversation Thread Continuity</h4>
            <p><strong>Have a multi-message conversation:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>Ask: "What is the ENCY system?"</li>
                <li>Follow-up: "How many tables does it have?"</li>
                <li>Follow-up: "Can you show me the Herb model?"</li>
                <li>Verify AI can maintain context across messages</li>
            </ol>

            <p><strong>Database Check:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>-- See the whole conversation
SELECT id, role, LEFT(content, 100) as content_preview, created_at
FROM ai_messages 
WHERE conversation_id = [YOUR_CONVERSATION_ID]
ORDER BY created_at ASC;</code></pre>

            <p style="color: #155724; background: #d4edda; padding: 10px; border-radius: 3px;">
                <strong>✅ Success:</strong> All 3+ messages should be linked under same conversation_id, maintaining order and context.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 3.4: Test Web Search Integration (If Enabled)</h4>
            <p><strong>Ask a question requiring external information:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>Send: "What's the latest Node.js LTS version?"</li>
                <li>Check if AI performs web search</li>
                <li>Verify web_search_results table has entries</li>
            </ol>

            <p><strong>Database Check:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SELECT id, query, result_title, result_url, found_by_user_id, created_at
FROM web_search_results 
ORDER BY created_at DESC 
LIMIT 5;</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Record:</strong> How many web search results? Are they relevant?</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Phase 4: Performance Testing -->
    <div class="content-section">
        <h2 id="phase-4-performance">⚡ Phase 4: Performance & Load Testing (Scaling Verification)</h2>

        <div class="phase-status">
            <span class="status-badge pending">EXECUTE TODAY</span>
            <p><strong>Execution:</strong> Test system performance with realistic loads</p>
            <p><strong>Duration Est.:</strong> 45 minutes</p>
        </div>

        <h3>Purpose</h3>
        <p>Verify the system can handle realistic usage: multiple messages, large conversations, heavy search activity.</p>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 4.1: Query Performance Baseline</h4>
            <p><strong>Measure query response times:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>-- Check query response time for conversation history (100 messages)
SELECT SQL_CALC_FOUND_ROWS id, role, LEFT(content, 50) as preview, created_at
FROM ai_messages 
WHERE conversation_id = [ID]
ORDER BY created_at DESC
LIMIT 100;

-- Check query time (should be < 100ms):
SHOW PROFILES;</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Verify:</strong> Query returns in under 100ms with proper indexes</p>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 4.2: FULLTEXT Search Performance</h4>
            <p><strong>Benchmark documentation search:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SELECT COUNT(*) as results
FROM documentation_metadata_index 
WHERE MATCH(searchable_text) AGAINST('database' IN BOOLEAN MODE);

-- Check execution time (should be < 50ms):</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Expected:</strong> Should return 50+ results in under 50ms with FULLTEXT index</p>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 4.3: Stress Test - Multiple Rapid Messages</h4>
            <p><strong>Send 10 rapid messages in same conversation:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>Create a new conversation</li>
                <li>Send 10 messages rapidly (one every 3-5 seconds)</li>
                <li>Measure time to save and retrieve each</li>
                <li>Check database for all messages</li>
            </ol>

            <p><strong>Verify:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>-- All 10 messages saved?
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ai_messages 
WHERE conversation_id = [ID];</code></pre>

            <p style="color: #155724; background: #d4edda; padding: 10px; border-radius: 3px;">
                <strong>✅ Success:</strong> All 10+ messages saved with correct timestamps and order preserved.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 4.4: Large Message Handling</h4>
            <p><strong>Test with large message content:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>Send a message with 5,000+ characters of content</li>
                <li>Verify it saves correctly to ai_messages (LONGTEXT column)</li>
                <li>Verify retrieval doesn't truncate or corrupt the content</li>
            </ol>

            <p><strong>Database Check:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SELECT id, LENGTH(content) as content_length, 
       CHAR_LENGTH(content) as char_count
FROM ai_messages 
WHERE LENGTH(content) > 5000
ORDER BY created_at DESC 
LIMIT 1;</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Verify:</strong> Length matches what you sent, no truncation</p>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 4.5: Index Effectiveness Check</h4>
            <p><strong>Verify indexes are being used efficiently:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>-- Check if queries use indexes
EXPLAIN SELECT * FROM ai_messages WHERE conversation_id = 1;
EXPLAIN SELECT * FROM documentation_metadata_index 
         WHERE MATCH(searchable_text) AGAINST('test' IN BOOLEAN MODE);</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Verify:</strong> EXPLAIN output shows "Using index" or reasonable key usage, not full table scans</p>
        </div>
    </div>

