    <!-- Success Criteria -->
    <div class="content-section">
        <h2 id="success-criteria">🎯 Success Criteria</h2>

        <div class="success-card">
            <h3>✅ FULL SUCCESS (All Phases Pass)</h3>
            <p><strong>Conditions:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Documentation search returns 50+ indexed files, FULLTEXT works</li>
                <li>Code search returns relevant results for function/method names</li>
                <li>AI Chat can reference documentation and code in responses</li>
                <li>Conversation threads maintain context across 5+ messages</li>
                <li>Performance: Queries < 100ms, FULLTEXT < 50ms, no index issues</li>
                <li>Stress test: 10 rapid messages all save and retrieve correctly</li>
                <li>Large messages (5000+ chars) save without truncation</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Next Step:</strong> Phase 5 cleanup, final testing, and production readiness review</p>
        </div>

        <div class="warning-card" style="background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; margin: 20px 0;">
            <h3>⚠️ PARTIAL SUCCESS (Some Features Missing)</h3>
            <p><strong>Conditions:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Search indexes exist but empty or incomplete</li>
                <li>Search works but performance slow (> 200ms)</li>
                <li>Integration works but with missing features (no web search, etc.)</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Next Step:</strong> Schedule Phase 5b (Optimization & Completion)</p>
        </div>

        <div class="alert alert-danger">
            <h3>❌ FAILURE (Critical Issues)</h3>
            <p><strong>Conditions:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Search indexes don't exist or are completely empty</li>
                <li>FULLTEXT queries fail or return no results</li>
                <li>AI Chat can't access search results</li>
                <li>Performance: Queries take > 1 second</li>
                <li>Stress test: Messages lost or corrupted</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Next Step:</strong> Debug search implementation and return to Phase 1</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Next Steps -->
    <div class="content-section">
        <h2 id="next-steps">🔄 Next Steps (December 28 & Beyond)</h2>

        <h3>If All Tests Pass ✅</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Phase 5:</strong> Documentation, cleanup, and production readiness</li>
            <li><strong>Phase 6:</strong> Monitor performance in production</li>
            <li><strong>Enhancement:</strong> Add web search integration (if not yet enabled)</li>
            <li><strong>Optimization:</strong> Fine-tune search relevance and performance</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>If Issues Found ⚠️</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Priority 1:</strong> Fix failing search features</li>
            <li><strong>Priority 2:</strong> Optimize performance (if > 200ms queries)</li>
            <li><strong>Priority 3:</strong> Complete missing features (web search, etc.)</li>
        </ul>

